  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Knowledge management and capacity building for advocacy about climate change in Central America</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve the knowledge management and capacity strengthening in analysis and advocacy, related to climate change, in the Central American region.

The 10 partner members of the livelihoods programme will be the direct beneficiaries, this number can be increased. The partners will select some members of the technical team and representative leaders, who will be trained by Centro Humboldt. Some of the topics will include:  identifying the causes and alternative strategies for climate change adaptation; promoting better adaptation practices through public policies and national strategies; promoting dialogue between civil society and government about climate change. 

The methodology is called cascading.  First at least 10 people (6 men and 4 women) from each partner will be trained, then those people will be replicated in their communities and institutions spreading the training.</narrative>
  </description>
